docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:161:    <p>A small fraction of spawned sessions die seconds after birth (an <strong>intermittent race</strong>, not an agent bug), and their row lingers forever as a zombie. Click it and you get zellij's raw "not found" piped straight into the panel.</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:168:  <p>You spawned <code>zj2tq9</code>. It appeared in the left rail under <em>yyork › Working</em>, looking like a healthy session. Clicking it painted the detail panel with:</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:211:    <p>The spawn write was legitimate. <code class="file">CreateSession</code> gates on <code class="file">waitForSessionUp</code>, which polls <code>zellij list-sessions</code> for up to 2.5s and rolls the whole spawn back if the name never shows. So <code>zj2tq9</code> <em>was</em> alive at <code>03:14:36</code>. It died later, and the row stayed. This is a lifecycle problem, not a bad insert.</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:217:  <p>Here is where the investigation almost went off a cliff. I reproduced spawns and they appeared to <em>vanish instantly</em>, every time. That turned out to be a measurement artifact, and understanding it is the key to the whole bug.</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:246:      <div class="node good"><div class="nh">yyork spawn</div><div class="nb">ConfigureSocketDir → creates session in<br><code>/tmp/zellij-501</code></div></div>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:258:    <h5>Sessions vanish the moment you spawn them</h5>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:265:  <p>The most tempting wrong turn. You re-ran with <code>--agent codex</code>, got <code>y3wjfr</code>, and it worked. Natural conclusion: claude-code is broken. So I spawned both, repeatedly, and watched them in the correct socket dir.</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:287:  <p>A small fraction of sessions die seconds after birth. It is intermittent and load-sensitive. I could not force it on command, 6/6 sequential and 11/11 parallel spawns all survived, yet <code>gw2r3e</code> and <code>zj2tq9</code> definitively died. That signature is a race in the create/teardown window.</p>
docs/ghost-session-investigation.html:322:        <p>Probe <code>SessionExists</code> once more after the client detaches and the teardown settles. If it is gone, fail the spawn and roll back instead of persisting a row for a session that did not survive its own birth. Closes the race at the source.</p>
